React setup
Install node js (backend env)
Install VS Studio
Create a new React folder and open in VS Studio
Open terminal in VS Studio and run the commands
npm create vite@latest
give a project name ex. my-react-app
select React then javascript
cd my-react-app
npm install
npm run dev
Server is running now and can be accessed via the localhost:port link

import React, {useState} from 'react';
const [var, setVar] = useState(initialVal);
const updateName = () => {
        setVar("New Val");
    }
use className instead of class(reserved)
<> code </> wrap code with fragment to return more than one element

display: flex;
flex-direction: (def: row) or column;
justify-content: center (main axis) ex. row will be horizontal axis
align-items: center (cross axis)

display: grid;
grid-template-columns/rows: 100px 100px 100px;

display: none or block; (removes element)
display: visible or hidden; (hides element, still takes up space)

@media screen and (max-width: 480px) { }

element.classList.add('new-class');

Storing and retrieving JSON
myObj = { "name":"Jane", "age":18, "city":"Chicago" };
myJSON = JSON.stringify(myObj);                 // storing data
localStorage.setItem("testJSON", myJSON);   
text = localStorage.getItem("testJSON");        // retrieving data 
obj = JSON.parse(text);
document.write(obj.name);

